1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - This paper deals with information theoretic secrecy in the many-to-one interference channel, which is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper introduces confidentiality in the many-to-one interference channel, which is a key aspect of cryptography and security. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The many-to-one interference channel is a type of interference network, which is a topic in social and information networks. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a communication channel, which is a core topic in networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although not directly related to multimedia, the paper deals with communication channels, which are often used for multimedia transmission.
